a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 4 / ((sqrt 5 + 1) * (root 4 5 + 1) * (root 8 5 + 1) * (root 16 5 + 1))"
shows  "(x + 1) powr 48 = 125"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Let $$x={4\over{(\sqrt5+1)(\root 4\of5+1)(\root 8\of5+1)(\root
{16}\of5+1)}}.$$Find $(x+1)^{48}$. The final Answer is 125
 ### Proof
 Multiplying the top and bottom by $\sqrt[16]{5} - 1$, we get a lot of simplification by difference-of-squares: \[\begin{aligned} x& = \frac{4(\sqrt[16]{5}-1)}{(\sqrt{5}+1)(\sqrt[4]{5}+1)(\sqrt[8]{5}+1)(\sqrt[16]{5}+1)(\sqrt[16]{5}-1)} \\ &= \frac{4(\sqrt[16]{5}-1)}{(\sqrt{5}+1)(\sqrt[4]{5}+1)(\sqrt[8]{5}+1)(\sqrt[8]{5}-1)} \\ &= \frac{4(\sqrt[16]{5}-1)}{(\sqrt{5}+1)(\sqrt[4]{5}+1)(\sqrt[4]{5}-1)} \\ &= \frac{4(\sqrt[16]{5}-1)}{(\sqrt{5}+1)(\sqrt{5}-1)} \\ &= \frac{4(\sqrt[16]{5}-1)}{4} = \sqrt[16]{5} - 1.
 \end{aligned}\]Thus, \[(x+1)^{48} = \left(\sqrt[16]{5}\right)^{48} = 5^3 = \boxed{125}.\]
 *)

theorem

shows  "(x + 1) powr 48 = 125"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
